[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Search ClickUp export import entire space workspace migration View Let me get more detailed information from ClickUp's official documentation on these methods: Using Tool | Read https://help.clickup.com/hc/en-us/articles/6311301775255-Duplicate-Spaces-Folders-and-Lists View Using Tool | Read https://help.clickup.com/hc/en-us/articles/6310551109527-Task-data-export View Using Tool | Read https://help.clickup.com/hc/en-us/articles/29806883199127-Consolidate-Workspaces View Now let me search for information about using templates to move data between workspaces: Using Tool | Search ClickUp share template migrate space between workspaces different accounts View Using Tool | Read https://help.clickup.com/hc/en-us/articles/6326130026519-Share-a-template View Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a detailed, tactical guide for you. Complete ClickUp Space Migration Guide: Moving Data Between Workspaces Good news - there are 3 primary methods to duplicate and move your ClickUp space to another workspace. Let me break down each option with step-by-step instructions. 📊 METHOD COMPARISON TABLE Method\tBest For\tWhat Gets Copied\tLimitations\tPlan Requirements\tTimeframe 1. Template Sharing\tMoving specific Spaces between different workspaces/accounts\tTasks, subtasks, descriptions, attachments, checklists, custom fields, docs\tAssignees/mentions only retained if users exist in destination workspace\tAny plan (Free Forever+)\tImmediate (self-service) 2. Duplicate Within Same Workspace\tCreating copies within your current workspace only\tComplete structure, settings, and data\tCannot move to different workspace - only duplicates in same location\tAny plan (Free Forever+)\tImmediate (self-service) 3. Official Workspace Consolidation\tFull workspace mergers with everything\tComplete migration including chat, integrations, all spaces\tRequires downtime (hours), source workspace gets archived, both workspaces must be owned by you\tAny plan, but destination must be same/higher tier\t1-3 days (requires ClickUp team assistance) ✅ RECOMMENDED METHOD: Template Sharing (Most Practical) This is your best option since you've been invited to a space (meaning it's in someone else's workspace) and you want to copy it to your own workspace. STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS Phase 1: Create Template from Source Space Step\tAction\tWhere to Click\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen ClickUp and navigate to the Space you want to copy\tSidebar > Find the Space name\tN/A\tYou'll see the Space opened with all its folders/lists 2\tAccess the Space menu\tHover over Space name in sidebar > Click three dots (...) icon OR right-click the Space name\tN/A\tDropdown menu appears 3\tCreate template\tClick \"Save as Template\" or \"Template Center\"\tN/A\tTemplate creation modal opens 4\tName your template\tEnter descriptive name\tExample: \"Marketing Space Backup - Dec 2025\"\tTemplate name saved 5\tConfigure what to include\tSelect checkboxes for what to copy: ☑️ Tasks ☑️ Subtasks ☑️ Descriptions ☑️ Attachments ☑️ Checklists ☑️ Custom Fields ☑️ Docs\tCheck all boxes you want to preserve\tTemplate settings configured 6\tSave template\tClick \"Create Template\" button\tN/A\tTemplate saved to Template Center Phase 2: Share Template Publicly Step\tAction\tWhere to Click\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 7\tOpen Template Center\tClick your profile/avatar > \"Template Center\"\tN/A\tTemplate library opens 8\tFind your template\tSearch or scroll to find template you just created\tTemplate name from Step 4\tTemplate preview appears 9\tOpen share settings\tClick \"Share\" button (upper-right corner)\tN/A\tShare Template modal opens 10\tEnable public sharing\tToggle \"Public sharing\" ON\tN/A\tPublic link becomes available 11\tCopy the link\tClick \"Copy Link\" button\tN/A\tLink copied to clipboard (https://sharing.clickup.com/...) 12\tSave this link\tPaste link into notepad or email to yourself\tLink from clipboard\tLink saved for next phase Phase 3: Import Template to Your Workspace Step\tAction\tWhere to Click\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 13\tSwitch to destination workspace\tClick workspace avatar (upper-left) > Select YOUR workspace\tYour workspace name\tYou're now in your own workspace 14\tOpen the shared link\tPaste the link from Step 12 into browser address bar > Press Enter\tTemplate sharing link\t\"Use a template\" modal opens 15\tVerify workspace\tConfirm dropdown shows YOUR workspace name\tIf not, select correct workspace\tCorrect destination confirmed 16\tName the Space\tEnter name for the new Space\tExample: \"Marketing Space (Imported)\"\tName configured 17\tChoose location\tSelect where to place it: - Root level of workspace - Inside existing Folder\tWorkspace root or specific folder\tLocation selected 18\tOptional: Save template copy\tCheck \"Also save a copy of this template\" if you want to reuse later\t☑️ if you want template saved ☐ if one-time use\tTemplate save preference set 19\tImport the Space\tClick \"Use Template\" button\tN/A\tSpace begins importing 20\tVerify import\tCheck your workspace sidebar for new Space\tN/A\tComplete Space structure appears with all data ⚠️ IMPORTANT CONSIDERATIONS What WILL Transfer: ✅ Complete Space structure (Folders, Lists) ✅ All tasks and subtasks ✅ Task descriptions and comments ✅ File attachments ✅ Checklists and checklist items ✅ Custom fields and values ✅ ClickUp Docs ✅ Due dates and date ranges ✅ Task priorities and statuses ✅ Tags ✅ Time estimates What WON'T Transfer (Limitations): ❌ Assignees - Only retained if the exact same users exist in destination workspace (with same email addresses) ❌ @Mentions - Will appear as plain text if users don't exist in destination ❌ Integrations - Need to be reconfigured in destination workspace ❌ Automations - Must be recreated ❌ Webhooks - Must be reconfigured ❌ Time tracking history - Time estimates transfer, but logged time tracking data doesn't ❌ Activity/audit logs - Start fresh in new workspace ALTERNATIVE: Bulk Export Method (For Data Backup) If you need to export data for records or to import into another tool, here's the bulk export process: CSV Export Steps Step\tAction\tWhere to Click\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tPlan Required 1\tAccess Workspace settings\tClick workspace avatar (upper-left) > \"Settings\"\tN/A\tSettings page opens\tAdmin/Owner role 2\tNavigate to export\tClick \"Imports/Exports\" in left sidebar\tN/A\tImport/Export page displays\tBusiness Plan+ for unlimited exports 3\tStart export process\tClick \"Export Items\" button\tN/A\tExport configuration page\tFree/Unlimited: 5 exports only 4\tSelect locations\tClick \"Select locations\" dropdown > Choose Spaces/Folders/Lists\tCheck boxes for what to export\tSelected items highlighted\tN/A 5\tStart export\tClick \"Start Export\" button\tN/A\tExport processing begins (may take minutes for large datasets)\tN/A 6\tDownload file\tClick \"Download Export\" when ready\tN/A\tCSV file downloads to computer\tN/A 7\tCheck email\tLook for email with download link (backup option)\tN/A\tEmail with CSV attachment arrives\tN/A CSV Export Includes: Task IDs, names, descriptions, statuses, dates, assignees, tags, priorities, attachments (URLs), time data, checklists, comments METHOD 3: Official Workspace Consolidation When to Use: You OWN both workspaces and need to merge everything permanently. Requirements Checklist Requirement\tStatus\tAction Needed You own BOTH workspaces (or have written owner approval)\t☐\tContact workspace owners All users from source workspace have joined destination\t☐\tInvite all members to destination first Destination workspace is same or higher plan tier\t☐\tUpgrade if needed You can tolerate 3-8 hours downtime\t☐\tSchedule off-peak time Custom Task ID prefixes don't conflict\t☐\tAudit both workspaces Process Steps Step\tAction\tTimeline\tNotes 1\tContact ClickUp support team\tImmediate\tEmail support@clickup.com or use in-app chat 2\tSubmit consolidation request\tSame day\tProvide both workspace URLs and owner approvals 3\tSchedule migration window\t1-3 days\tClickUp will coordinate off-peak time 4\tPre-migration prep\tBefore scheduled time\tMatch ClickApps, create custom fields, set up integrations in destination 5\tMigration occurs\t3-8 hours\tBoth workspaces offline during process 6\tVerify data in destination\tImmediately after\tCheck all Spaces, tasks, custom fields 7\tSource workspace archived\tAutomatic\tCan request access from support if needed 🎯 RECOMMENDED ACTION PLAN FOR YOUR SITUATION Since you've been invited to someone else's Space, here's my tactical recommendation: Option A: You Have Permission to Create Template (Recommended) DO THIS: Tonight: Follow Template Sharing Method (15-20 minutes) Create template from their Space Enable public sharing, copy link Import to your workspace Result: Complete copy of everything in your control Rationale: Self-service, immediate, no permissions needed for import phase, retains all structure and data Option B: You Don't Have Template Creation Rights DO THIS: Ask the workspace owner to create the template and share the public link with you Provide them with Phase 1 & 2 instructions above Once you receive link, complete Phase 3 yourself Result: Same outcome, requires minimal cooperation Rationale: Most workspace owners are happy to share templates; it's non-destructive to their workspace Option C: Export for Reference Only DO THIS: If you only need data backup (not working copy), request CSV export Workspace admin runs export process You receive CSV file with all task data Result: Spreadsheet with all information (but not \"live\" ClickUp environment) Rationale: Good for analysis, reporting, or importing to different tool; not for continuing work in ClickUp 🔍 VERIFICATION CHECKLIST After migration, verify these elements: Item to Check\tHow to Verify\tExpected Result Space structure\tCount Folders/Lists in both locations\tNumbers match Task count\tUse \"Everything\" view with task counter\tTotal tasks match Attachments\tSpot-check 5-10 tasks with files\tAll files accessible Custom fields\tCheck task details view\tAll custom fields present with data Docs\tNavigate to Docs view\tAll docs appear with formatting Due dates\tView Calendar or Timeline\tDates preserved accurately Task hierarchy\tCheck subtask relationships\tParent-child links intact 💡 OPTIMIZATION TIPS Before Migration: Clean up source Space - Archive completed tasks you don't need Document custom configurations - Screenshot custom field settings, automations, views Export member list - Note who needs access in destination workspace After Migration: Reassign tasks - Manually reassign tasks to correct team members in new workspace Recreate automations - Set up any workflow automations from scratch Configure integrations - Reconnect Slack, Google Drive, etc. Update bookmarks - Replace any bookmarked URLs with new workspace URLs Cost Optimization: Free Plan users: You get 5 exports - use wisely or upgrade to Business Plan for unlimited Template method is FREE on all plans - no export limits Consolidation service is free but requires both workspaces owned by you 📞 SUPPORT RESOURCES Issue\tResource\tLink General migration help\tClickUp Help Center\thelp.clickup.com Workspace consolidation\tContact Support\tsupport@clickup.com or in-app chat Template sharing issues\tHelp Article\thelp.clickup.com/hc/en-us/articles/6326130026519 Export problems\tHelp Article\thelp.clickup.com/hc/en-us/articles/6310551109527 NEXT STEPS Choose your path based on this decision tree: Copy Do you own the source workspace? │ ├─ YES → Need to merge ENTIRE workspaces? │         │ │         ├─ YES → Use Method 3 (Consolidation) - Contact ClickUp Support │         └─ NO → Use Method 1 (Template Sharing) │ └─ NO → Can you create templates in source workspace? │ ├─ YES → Use Method 1 (Template Sharing) - Do it yourself ├─ NO → Ask owner to share template link with you └─ ONLY NEED DATA → Request CSV export from admin My recommendation: Start with Template Sharing Method (Method 1) - it's the most practical, immediate, and doesn't require special permissions or support tickets. Time estimate: 15-20 minutes total for complete migration using templates. Would you like me to: Create a visual flowchart of the template sharing process? Generate a checklist document you can save for reference? Help you draft a message to request template creation from the workspace owner? Let me know your specific situation (whether you can create templates in the source workspace) and I'll provide the exact next steps! Super Agent Your AI Employee Free Trial +13 Ultra Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=284a7b16-dd54-4d8f-8828-cd9fa781f135","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=284a7b16-dd54-4d8f-8828-cd9fa781f135"}]}]}]
